# Markdown authoring constraints

These apply when editing or creating markdown files in this workspace.

## Register

- No hype. No prestige language. No ideological labeling.
- Short paragraphs. Precise language. Structural clarity over persuasive flourish.
- Use em dashes only when they improve structural clarity. Prefer shorter sentences.
- No semicolons in published prose.
- Restraint is not silence. Say less, more carefully.

## Structure

- Use explicit headings. Prefer flat structure over deep nesting.
- Keep sections short enough to read without scrolling.
- If a section needs more than three levels of heading, consider splitting it.

## Licensing

- Seed texts and authored content are CC BY 4.0.
- Code and tooling are MIT.
- Do not remove or weaken license notices.

